Love life with this lady so much. Superstar wife, momma and boss woman. We can have a blast anywhere, whether it’s at home on the farm or out on the town having some boujee sushi. It doesn’t matter. I don’t need an outing or a big event to enjoy her presence. Just sitting in the tub having a meaningful reflection about life gives me so much joy. Many times I’ll express my failures or lack of purpose to her and she swiftly reminds me of my value and love for me no matter what. How did the girl in my HS sociology class end up being such a diamond? God really looked out for me. @alexysgabrielle

When I got to LA I hardly had enough money for even one month or rent. If it weren’t for some incredible friends (@andypagana @mattlfahey @joekeenfahey) letting me crash in studios / couches, I would have never survived. However, I needed to come up with some cash to continue being able to eat and eventually afford a room to rent. So I had to get down to business, work a couple gigs and hustle to get by for a bit. My song ‘99 Civic’ tells the story from that era of my life.

married for 9 years. Why does it feel like we’re still kids though?! If I can be frank, marriage is bliss with this woman. It’s just been easy because we know each other so well and have unwavering support for each other. Most importantly, our marriage is centered around Christ and the vows we committed to upholding. We pick each other up when the other is feeling hopeless. Sure it’s been hard to spend as much one on one time since becoming parents but we’re still consciously setting time to date each other. But I don’t need a night out or a dinner reservation to enjoy her company. We can talk for hours about our life and family. She is my best friend, and anything in my life that is funny, exciting, devastating or problematic, I approach her first. I know I’m not the perfect husband, but I promise to strive to be the best I can be because that’s what you deserve. Love you, mama. I know we don’t have a babysitter tonight @alexysgabrielle so, tub date? 🛁
